A prominent human rights lawyer in Lesotho has had to have medical treatment after being abducted and tortured by police, while another lawyer went into hiding after police threatened to kill him, report Mohalenyane Phakela and 'Marafaele Mohloboli for the Lesotho Times. The country's chief justice has taken judicial notice of the abuse in an extraordinary judgment refusing to recuse himself from presiding over the trial, reports Carmel Rickard for Legalbrief.